pageContext.claim: “Unemployment has reached the lowest rate in 51 years and soon it will be in the history of our country. 51 years.”
pageContext.analysis: The unemployment rate was 3.7 percent in November 2018. Since then it has picked up, hitting 4 percent in January 2019 then to 3.8 percent in February 2019. The unemployment rate is now only the lowest in six months.
